Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/src/H5Dscatgath.c\n+++ b/src/H5Dscatgath.c\n@@ -648,8 +648,13 @@\n     assert(io_info);\n     assert(dset_info);\n     assert(dset_info->mem_space);\n     assert(dset_info->file_space);\n-    assert(dset_info->buf.cvp);\n+    if (!dset_info->buf.cvp) {\n+        HGOTO_ERROR(H5E_ARGS, H5E_BADVALUE, FAIL, "NULL buffer pointer passed to H5D__scatgath_write");\n+    }\n \n     /* Set buf pointer */\n     buf = dset_info->buf.cvp;\n'}`
responded: The root cause is that the assertion `assert(dset_info->buf.cvp);` at line 653 is being optimized out in release builds, so the code continues and dereferences `dset_info->buf.cvp` (via `buf`) in both the gather and optimized write paths, even if it is NULL. The sanitizer report shows the crash is still at the optimized write path.

**Key Fix:**  
- The check for `dset_info->buf.cvp` being NULL must be performed at the very start of the function, before any use or assignment to `buf`, and must return an error if NULL.
- Remove the assertion and replace it with a runtime check and error return.

**Patch:**
```diff
--- a/src/H5Dscatgath.c
+++ b/src/H5Dscatgath.c
@@ -648,8 +648,13 @@
     assert(io_info);
     assert(dset_info);
     assert(dset_info->mem_space);
     assert(dset_info->file_space);
-    assert(dset_info->buf.cvp);
+    if (!dset_info->buf.cvp) {
+        HGOTO_ERROR(H5E_ARGS, H5E_BADVALUE, FAIL, "NULL buffer pointer passed to H5D__scatgath_write");
+    }

     /* Set buf pointer */
     buf = dset_info->buf.cvp;
```
This ensures that no code path in this function can ever dereference a NULL buffer pointer.

